<---------------------------------Explaination---------------------------------------->

1. What is an Exception
-> Exception ka matlab hai disruptive event matlab kuch galat hojana code me and wo galti kem karan
hamra code ye bolta hai ki ye se aab aage nhai bhada jaeyga flow ko inpterupt ho chuka hai
isko handle karo or system ko batao ki iss error ko aise handel karo and hamra programm ka flow
tode na chalne de ...
-> uppar wala jo error ko handel kar raha hai usi ko ham bolte hai exception handling
-> Exception ek taraha ka object hi hai jaise apan ne dheka ta ki array ke andar hamra error
aaya tha to terminal me error aaya tha with name of array index of bound exception in it throw
kiya tha java me exception hamrai galti pe is error me hamko exception ki type batai jati hai
kya type tha and bhot kuch .
-> chart ke andar throwable hai usme do chiz hai ERROR and EXCEPTION
-> ERROR ye apni galti ke karan nhai hota ye hota system ke galti ke karan jaise memory full
hojana and system ke kuch issue ke karan se hota hai isme hamara koi haat nhai hota .
-> EXCEPTION ye apni galti ke karan hota hai jaise khai pe error aana ye hamne galat logic
lhik diya ho uske wjaha iske do type hai runtime exception and compile time exception .

2. Try-Catch
-> Try-Catch iska matlab hai ki hamko pata hai ki esme error ane wali to wo error handel kaise karna
hai wo try-catch ki madat se handel karenge jise ham bolte hai exception handling .
-> try ke andar jo bhi ham lhikte hai wo exception aane ki shambhavna rehti hai agar code me
exception aajaye to java direct exception throw na kare isliye ham catch ka use karenge catch(Arti
hmatcException exception){sout("gadbad hogai")} iska matlab hai ki agar mera try ka code me exception
aaya to me catch me jo bhi lhikunga wo chal jaeyga and catch ke andar ham aapna exception ko
handle kar rhae honge .
-> agar hamko lagta hai ki hamra code me exception aa shakti to wo particular code ham try ke
andar lhikenge and catch me usko handel karlenge .

3. Types of Exception
-> i) User defined exception ii) built in exception
<-------- explaination -------->
i) User defined exception :- ye exception ham banate hai .
ii) built in exception
-> ye wo exception hai jo java provide karta hai phele se hi phele se hi built hoke aai hui exception
by java .
i) checked exception :- ye exception handel karna ya to declare karna  complusory hai
-> ye ham log try catch ki madat se kar shakte hai.
-> ya to declare kar shake hai throws ki madat se .
-> throws ham log kisi ke shaat bhi declare kar shakte hai chaye wo checked ho ya unchecked .
ii) unchecked exception :- ye exception handel karna jarruri nhai because ye java hamko direct
throw kardega bina hamare handel kiye .

4. Throw and Throws
--> Throws :-  ye apne method ke name ke shat use hoga .
-> ye apne method ke aage lhik te hai ye bata ta hai ki ye method ye name ka exception
de shakta hai ya to iss name exception aa shakti hai .
-> isme hamko try catch ka use nhai karna padta kyu ki ye phele hi bata deta hai ki exception
aa shakti hai .
-> ye sirf ye bata ta hai ki iske andar se exception originate hi shakti hai .
-> baki ka notes ke andar point hai wo read karle .
-> ye apne try catch se bachne ke liye use hota hai .
--> Throw :- ye apne new key word ke shat aayega matlab ki new shaat ayega .
-> agar ham chhate hai ki uss exception ke baad hamara code chale hi na to ham throws or throw ka use
karenge .
-> throws hame bata hai ki iss type ka exception aaa shakta hai ye thow se ham uss exception
ko actual me throw kardenge
-> Calculator wale me jake dhek usme bhaut ache se shmajaya hai stack trease .
-> thore ke andar ham jo new se lhik te hai usko bolte hai ki ham exception ka object throw
kar rhae hai .
-> iska difference bata gya hai notes me wo jake dhek le shamaj aajayega

5. Finally Block
-> ye try catch ke shaat lhika jata hai ye agar ham log ne lhik diya to iska matlab hai ki
finally block chalega hi chalega bhale hi kitni exception aai ho ya na aayi ho ye chalega
to chalega hi .

